1
00:00:15,118 --> 00:00:16,560
I know everything,

2
00:00:17,640 --> 00:00:19,288
that my husband hired you to sleep with me.

3
00:00:19,341 --> 00:00:21,960
- It's not like that, Ms. Shen.
- But I saw him paid you.

4
00:00:22,387 --> 00:00:23,388
What do you need to tell me?

5
00:00:23,566 --> 00:00:25,480
Mr. Perm told me that he needed a baby

6
00:00:25,534 --> 00:00:26,840
but he couldn't make one himself.

7
00:00:27,144 --> 00:00:29,960
Perm happened to hear his dad changed his will.

8
00:00:30,240 --> 00:00:33,000
The assets will belong to Mr. Perm and Mr. Term,

9
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,560
when they have children only.

10
00:00:36,128 --> 00:00:38,320
The messes happened because him wanting Dad's assets?

11
00:00:38,438 --> 00:00:39,640
What about the death of Shin?

12
00:00:39,650 --> 00:00:41,160
When Shin found out about us,

13
00:00:41,307 --> 00:00:42,800
he decided to kill him instead.

14
00:00:44,694 --> 00:00:46,160
Was it necessary?

15
00:00:46,422 --> 00:00:47,560
I don't trust him.

16
00:00:47,995 --> 00:00:49,440
that he must be furious

17
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:51,200
that we run away like this.

18
00:00:51,392 --> 00:00:52,520
You're going to run away with me?

19
00:00:52,544 --> 00:00:53,545
We will run together.

20
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:54,921
Just the three of us.

21
00:00:55,035 --> 00:00:57,436
Dad. Mom. And the baby.

22
00:00:57,563 --> 00:00:59,040
Let's run away to Hat Yai together.

23
00:00:59,339 --> 00:01:01,920
He won't find us for sure.

24
00:01:02,523 --> 00:01:04,524
He is about to leave us, dear.

25
00:01:04,774 --> 00:01:06,200
You need to say goodbye to him properly.

26
00:01:06,662 --> 00:01:07,553
He is not dying.

27
00:01:07,595 --> 00:01:08,700
- What are you doing?
- Aunt Erb.

28
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:09,721
I told you to get the doctor.

29
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:12,240
You can't die! You can't!

30
00:01:17,544 --> 00:01:18,641
You did a great job.

31
00:01:19,339 --> 00:01:21,240
Your dad's heart comes back to normal now.

32
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,481
Thank you so much.

33
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:26,761
Is there any other way

34
00:01:26,784 --> 00:01:28,880
to prevent this situation to happen again?

35
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:31,881
I need to tell you frankly

36
00:01:33,483 --> 00:01:35,040
that your dad has been in this stage for so long.

37
00:01:36,016 --> 00:01:38,440
His interntal system can't be functioned normally.

38
00:01:39,168 --> 00:01:40,480
What we did today

39
00:01:40,939 --> 00:01:42,160
was just temporary.

40
00:01:44,275 --> 00:01:45,440
Did you see that?

41
00:01:46,136 --> 00:01:47,840
Your dad wasn't supposed to be here.

42
00:01:48,350 --> 00:01:51,080
We can't force the nature for so long.

43
00:02:01,614 --> 00:02:03,360
Your job is to cure patients.

44
00:02:03,854 --> 00:02:05,960
You need to prolong his life as long as you can.

45
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:08,441
I don't care how much it costs, he needs to live.

46
00:02:08,481 --> 00:02:10,042
This is not about money,

47
00:02:11,647 --> 00:02:13,640
but it depends on your dad's body.

48
00:02:16,462 --> 00:02:17,840
I don't care what you have to do

49
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,200
but my dad can't die. You hear me?

50
00:02:20,261 --> 00:02:21,262
I need him alive.

51
00:04:55,835 --> 00:04:58,080
I've never thought that you would love Dad this much.

52
00:04:59,611 --> 00:05:01,200
You wouldn't let him go.

53
00:05:04,606 --> 00:05:05,647
Is there something going on?

54
00:05:06,079 --> 00:05:07,080
Nothing.

55
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:10,090
I just want him to be with us for so long,

56
00:05:11,539 --> 00:05:13,540
to be a big tree, covering all of us.

57
00:05:15,646 --> 00:05:16,647
I am not you,

58
00:05:17,688 --> 00:05:19,189
you can't wait for Dad to be gone.

59
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:01,921
It will be dark soon.

60
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:05,040
Should we find a place to spend a night?

61
00:06:07,747 --> 00:06:09,840
We could ask for villagers' help.

62
00:06:11,336 --> 00:06:13,100
And we will continue our journey tomorrow.

63
00:06:16,192 --> 00:06:17,193
Sure.

64
00:06:50,643 --> 00:06:51,644
Excuse me?

65
00:06:52,910 --> 00:06:53,911
Is anybody home?

66
00:06:54,595 --> 00:06:55,596
Yeah?

67
00:06:56,168 --> 00:06:57,169
I'm coming.

68
00:07:01,075 --> 00:07:02,076
Can I help you?

69
00:07:03,315 --> 00:07:06,360
My wife and I are driving by and it's about to get dark.

70
00:07:07,078 --> 00:07:08,880
Can we spend a night here?

71
00:07:10,150 --> 00:07:11,800
When it's dawn, we will get going.

72
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,801
Can we?

73
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:16,481
Who's here, Mom?

74
00:07:17,414 --> 00:07:19,700
They are asking to spend a night here.

75
00:07:20,075 --> 00:07:21,076
They are?

76
00:07:23,526 --> 00:07:24,527
What do you think?

77
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,081
I think we can host them.

78
00:07:32,142 --> 00:07:34,120
What's wrong with your arm?

79
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,681
This one?

80
00:07:40,123 --> 00:07:42,040
I picked up some fruits by roadside.

81
00:07:43,307 --> 00:07:44,400
And my arm got scratches by their thorns.

82
00:07:45,286 --> 00:07:46,840
I see, thorns?

83
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:51,520
But our house is small, I hope it's okay.

84
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:54,837
Sure, we're not picky.

85
00:07:56,131 --> 00:07:57,132
Follow me.

86
00:07:58,195 --> 00:07:59,196
Thank you.

87
00:07:59,490 --> 00:08:00,560
I'll get your bag.

88
00:08:04,606 --> 00:08:05,640
You drove a car?

89
00:08:06,771 --> 00:08:08,400
This is so nice. Is it yours?

90
00:08:08,707 --> 00:08:10,640
I…that's right.

91
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:14,520
My dad bought it for us, for our wedding's gift.

92
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,280
Look at her.

93
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:20,350
Her skin is flawless, can't you see?

94
00:08:20,556 --> 00:08:22,080
I can tell that they're rich.

95
00:08:22,192 --> 00:08:24,160
- You're so stupid.
- Yeah, yeah.

96
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,520
Let's go. Follow me inside.

97
00:08:26,678 --> 00:08:28,080
I'll take you to your bedroom.

98
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,841
- Okay.
- Follow me.

99
00:08:30,107 --> 00:08:31,108
Just go.

100
00:08:33,531 --> 00:08:34,680
Please pick up wood.

101
00:08:38,048 --> 00:08:39,049
Follow me.

102
00:08:41,467 --> 00:08:42,468
Oh, come on!

103
00:08:44,064 --> 00:08:45,442
I have to do everything, right?

104
00:09:00,315 --> 00:09:03,160
Nopphorn? I need your help.

105
00:09:13,043 --> 00:09:14,325
We're so lucky today.

106
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:18,320
It'd be so nice to see kind people along the way every day.

107
00:09:22,512 --> 00:09:24,150
If we can't find a place to sleep at night,

108
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,520
we can sleep in the car.

109
00:09:28,539 --> 00:09:30,400
You can sleep on my arm.

110
00:09:33,835 --> 00:09:34,960
That's so romantic.

111
00:09:50,392 --> 00:09:53,715
I think that now we're a couple

112
00:09:54,275 --> 00:09:55,960
you need to stop calling me 'Ms. Shen'.

113
00:09:59,763 --> 00:10:00,764
What's that?

114
00:10:02,179 --> 00:10:03,570
Call me 'Shen'.

115
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,761
Just try it. Call me 'Shen'.

116
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,321
I…

117
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:12,681
Shen…

118
00:10:14,910 --> 00:10:16,320
I can't do it.

119
00:10:17,109 --> 00:10:18,920
I can't call you like that.

120
00:10:20,182 --> 00:10:22,640
Well, if you call me Ms. Shen,

121
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:25,560
then I will call you Mr. Tone.

122
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:27,401
Ms. Shen.

123
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,721
Mr. Tone.

124
00:10:28,936 --> 00:10:30,600
- Ms. Shen.
- Mr. Tone.

125
00:10:30,829 --> 00:10:32,462
- Ms. Shen.
- Mr. Tone.

126
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:33,521
- Ms. Shen.
- Mr. Tone.

127
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,001
Ms. Shen.

128
00:10:41,774 --> 00:10:42,775
Ms. Shen!

129
00:10:43,043 --> 00:10:44,400
Come here, where do you think you're going?

130
00:11:04,362 --> 00:11:05,363
From now on,

131
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,360
we can express our love

132
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:10,401
and we don't need to hide it anymore.

133
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:14,561
Sure,

134
00:11:14,843 --> 00:11:15,844
Mr. Tone.

135
00:12:11,859 --> 00:12:14,280
You can eat more if you want.

136
00:12:14,504 --> 00:12:17,200
- Eat up, come on.
- Thank you.

137
00:12:17,416 --> 00:12:19,560
We still have a big pot of rice in the kitchen.

138
00:12:20,886 --> 00:12:21,887
It's fine, thanks.

139
00:12:22,203 --> 00:12:24,000
We can barely finish all of this.

140
00:12:25,195 --> 00:12:26,480
Eat up.

141
00:12:26,957 --> 00:12:28,181
Here is hibiscus juice.

142
00:12:28,987 --> 00:12:30,680
- Why don't you try it.
- Thanks.

143
00:12:30,854 --> 00:12:31,855
Refreshing.

144
00:12:31,979 --> 00:12:33,880
I made it myself, just try it.

145
00:12:34,310 --> 00:12:35,311
Not too sweet.

146
00:12:39,132 --> 00:12:40,133
How was it.

147
00:12:41,520 --> 00:12:42,640
So refreshing.

148
00:12:42,774 --> 00:12:44,560
- See? I told you.
- You should finish it all.

149
00:12:44,598 --> 00:12:45,600
Am I right?

150
00:12:45,798 --> 00:12:48,000
Go on, eat up.

151
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,280
There are no juice for you and Daeng?

152
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:54,160
I…no need to.

153
00:12:54,267 --> 00:12:55,700
You two should drink it.

154
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:57,440
We drink it every day.

155
00:12:57,521 --> 00:12:58,960
- We're bored of it already.
- That's right.

156
00:12:59,088 --> 00:13:01,000
Go on, finish it up.

157
00:13:01,010 --> 00:13:02,100
It's so refreshing, isn't it?

158
00:13:02,315 --> 00:13:04,000
You think so?

159
00:13:06,528 --> 00:13:08,960
- Refreshing.
- So refreshing.

160
00:13:09,174 --> 00:13:10,400
What are we waiting for?

161
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:12,320
We should start eating already.

162
00:13:13,445 --> 00:13:14,100
Come on.

163
00:13:14,102 --> 00:13:15,480
Wow! My favorite.

164
00:13:16,432 --> 00:13:17,960
Of course, these are your favorite dishes.

165
00:13:23,403 --> 00:13:24,520
- Thank you.
- Sure.

166
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:27,201
Have some veggies.

167
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:50,203
Your sister-in-law has gone missing

168
00:13:50,448 --> 00:13:51,632
and you couldn't sleep?

169
00:13:52,875 --> 00:13:54,080
Can you stop with your sarcasm?

170
00:13:56,256 --> 00:13:57,720
My brother is acting so suspicious

171
00:13:58,584 --> 00:13:59,585
when it comes to Dad.

172
00:14:02,254 --> 00:14:03,320
What do you mean?

173
00:14:05,875 --> 00:14:07,600
He seems so caring about Dad.

174
00:14:08,819 --> 00:14:10,600
Dad was about to rest and he wouldn't let him.

175
00:14:12,408 --> 00:14:13,409
Actually,

176
00:14:14,526 --> 00:14:15,560
he has been acting weird since that day,

177
00:14:16,936 --> 00:14:18,320
the day that Dad became like this.

178
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:20,560
Why are you so obsessed over your assets?

179
00:14:21,072 --> 00:14:22,320
You can keep only a few coins in your mouth when you're dead.

180
00:14:22,923 --> 00:14:23,924
You need to know that

181
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,320
you are a hindrance of your children's success.

182
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:28,920
Term! Term!

183
00:14:29,062 --> 00:14:30,980
- What are you going to do to me?
- You ungrateful son!

184
00:14:31,131 --> 00:14:33,000
- You're so ungrateful.
- What will you do to me?

185
00:14:35,190 --> 00:14:36,450
What will you do to me?

186
00:14:38,006 --> 00:14:39,007
Dad?

187
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:41,600
Dad! Dad! Dad!

188
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,400
What is going on? What happens to him?

189
00:14:43,574 --> 00:14:45,800
Dad? What is going on?

190
00:14:45,926 --> 00:14:48,390
- Dad! Dad! Dad!
- Term!

191
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:49,401
What did you do to him?

192
00:14:49,472 --> 00:14:50,473
- I didn't do anything.
- Dad.

193
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:52,560
- Take a deep breath.
- He became this way all of a sudden.

194
00:14:53,662 --> 00:14:55,240
Is anybody here? Duang?

195
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:57,481
Duang, get the car ready.

196
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:58,656
Take Dad to the hospital.

197
00:14:59,062 --> 00:15:00,600
Stop looking and help me!

198
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:03,960
- You need to be fine, Dad!
- Dad.

199
00:16:10,563 --> 00:16:11,564
Ms. Shen.

200
00:16:12,923 --> 00:16:13,924
You need to wake up.

201
00:16:14,563 --> 00:16:15,566
It's almost one in the afternoon.

202
00:16:16,303 --> 00:16:17,400
We need to get going.

203
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:20,101
Almost one in the afternoon?

204
00:16:21,110 --> 00:16:23,080
I've never slept in this late before.

205
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:30,400
My head hurts, this feels weird.

206
00:16:32,854 --> 00:16:34,160
You feel that too?

207
00:16:36,595 --> 00:16:38,000
We must be exhausted from traveling,

208
00:16:38,740 --> 00:16:39,741
that's why we slept like a log.

209
00:16:41,310 --> 00:16:42,680
We should clean up

210
00:16:43,459 --> 00:16:44,460
so we could feel better.

211
00:16:58,203 --> 00:16:59,710
Daeng! Hurry!

212
00:16:59,811 --> 00:17:01,600
- Hey!
- Hey!

213
00:17:01,672 --> 00:17:04,526
Oh my! Why are you in such a hurry?

214
00:17:04,547 --> 00:17:06,720
- Let's eat first.
- That's right.

215
00:17:07,368 --> 00:17:10,150
We don't want to trouble you, we can eat somewhere else.

216
00:17:10,392 --> 00:17:12,320
It's such a long way to the market.

217
00:17:12,393 --> 00:17:14,000
- That's right.
- Let's eat here first.

218
00:17:14,051 --> 00:17:16,252
- My mom cooked a lot of food.
- It really is fine.

219
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:18,960
- We're in a hurry.
- Hurry? Where to?

220
00:17:18,979 --> 00:17:21,440
- No need to be hurry.
- My mom cooked grilled chicken.

221
00:17:21,507 --> 00:17:22,760
- Grilled fish.
- Yup, grilled fish.

222
00:17:22,808 --> 00:17:26,440
- I cooked it since early morning, let's eat.
- Thank you.

223
00:17:26,867 --> 00:17:28,720
Tone! Police!

224
00:17:30,166 --> 00:17:31,408
Hey! Where are you going?

225
00:17:31,675 --> 00:17:33,120
I knew it.

226
00:17:33,344 --> 00:17:35,560
- You two are robbers, aren't you?
- No, we're not.

227
00:17:35,659 --> 00:17:38,920
If not, then you need to talk to the police.

228
00:17:39,734 --> 00:17:40,735
I'm sorry.

229
00:17:41,030 --> 00:17:42,480
- Officer!
- Let me go.

230
00:17:44,571 --> 00:17:45,760
- Mom!
- Ms. Shen.

231
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,320
Officer! Officer!

232
00:17:54,592 --> 00:17:56,200
They went that way! Get them!

233
00:17:56,544 --> 00:17:57,545
That way!

234
00:18:00,147 --> 00:18:02,000
- Daeng!
- Mom!

235
00:18:06,014 --> 00:18:08,400
They must have put sleeping pills in our dinner last night.

236
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:09,801
that's why we slept like a log.

237
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:11,301
I think so.

238
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:13,760
Can you speed up?

239
00:18:13,976 --> 00:18:15,200
The police car is right behind us.

240
00:18:26,723 --> 00:18:27,724
Mr. Perm?

241
00:18:34,566 --> 00:18:37,480
Tone, get out of the vehicle.

242
00:18:39,456 --> 00:18:41,040
You're surrounded by officers.

243
00:18:47,320 --> 00:18:48,321
What should we do?

244
00:18:50,518 --> 00:18:52,160
We need to get out of the car.

245
00:19:00,454 --> 00:19:01,455
Hands above your head.

246
00:19:05,216 --> 00:19:06,217
Sit down.

247
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:09,881
What are you doing?

248
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:11,240
- Why are you arresting him?
- Ms. Shen, it's fine.

249
00:19:11,334 --> 00:19:13,000
- Ms. Shen.
- Come here.

250
00:19:19,739 --> 00:19:21,160
I found your money, sir.

251
00:19:22,950 --> 00:19:24,360
Tone Chartchartree.

252
00:19:26,246 --> 00:19:27,600
You are under arrest on theft charge,

253
00:19:28,107 --> 00:19:30,240
you stole Lord Samphanpanich's money and car.

254
00:19:30,688 --> 00:19:32,040
Also, you are under arrest from

255
00:19:32,571 --> 00:19:34,120
murdering Shin Sookdone.

256
00:19:34,683 --> 00:19:36,684
- Will you accept these charges?
- Not true!

257
00:19:36,923 --> 00:19:38,924
This is not true. I didn't kill Shin.

258
00:19:39,003 --> 00:19:40,880
- No!
- I didn't kill Shin.

259
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:42,480
He didn't do it, Officer.

260
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:44,000
We have solid evidence to arrest you.

261
00:19:44,379 --> 00:19:45,280
Go!

262
00:19:45,296 --> 00:19:46,760
No!

263
00:19:46,955 --> 00:19:48,360
Mr. Perm killed Shin.

264
00:19:48,502 --> 00:19:50,570
- He killed Shin.
- You shouldn't run away.

265
00:19:50,736 --> 00:19:52,480
You're man, you should own up to what you did.

266
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:55,440
You were so furious at him for asking you to sleep with him

267
00:19:55,522 --> 00:19:56,700
that you decided to murder him.

268
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:58,641
This is not true.

269
00:19:58,803 --> 00:20:00,200
I've never thought about killing him.

270
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:02,721
It was you who killed him, wanting to shut him up.

271
00:20:03,763 --> 00:20:04,764
Tone!

272
00:20:05,006 --> 00:20:07,283
You need to stop defaming Mr. Perm already

273
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,300
or your penalty will be harsher than this.

274
00:20:09,474 --> 00:20:10,715
I was framed!

275
00:20:10,747 --> 00:20:12,043
I was framed!

276
00:20:12,272 --> 00:20:15,480
- He framed me!
- Officers, get him to the police station.

277
00:20:15,606 --> 00:20:16,760
He is a stubborn criminal

278
00:20:16,891 --> 00:20:18,360
and you need a tough way to investigate him.

279
00:20:18,841 --> 00:20:20,280
I will take care of my wife from here.

280
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:21,561
Yes, sir.

281
00:20:21,667 --> 00:20:24,468
- Come on.
- I didn't kill him. Ms. Shen!

282
00:20:24,715 --> 00:20:26,960
- Tone!
- I didn't kill him.

283
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:30,630
Get in! Go!

284
00:20:36,819 --> 00:20:37,820
Let me go.

285
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:43,240
I've never thought that you can be this cruel.

286
00:20:44,176 --> 00:20:45,177
Just you wait,

287
00:20:45,610 --> 00:20:47,640
the truth will come that that you were the one

288
00:20:47,690 --> 00:20:48,691
who killed Shin,

289
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:49,960
not Tone!

290
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,520
Who do you think the police will believe? Me or Tone?

291
00:20:52,576 --> 00:20:54,000
I have my friends in the police department.

292
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:57,841
- Go back home with me.
- I won't.

293
00:21:00,636 --> 00:21:02,090
I know everything.

294
00:21:03,918 --> 00:21:05,520
I can't be with a crafty

295
00:21:05,651 --> 00:21:07,440
and a cruel person like you.

296
00:21:07,450 --> 00:21:08,800
I'm glad you know that I am cruel.

297
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:11,161
And I can be even more cruel.

298
00:21:11,180 --> 00:21:13,240
I can order officers to give harsh penalty to Tone

299
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:15,381
- I can even ask them to shoot him to death!
- Don't do that!

300
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:24,760
Go home with me.

301
00:21:25,923 --> 00:21:27,640
Be my wife like you used to

302
00:21:29,150 --> 00:21:31,640
and I will save Tone from being executed. Okay?

303
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:37,920
You don't have to think about it.

304
00:21:38,774 --> 00:21:40,120
Just go home with me

305
00:21:41,390 --> 00:21:43,000
and you can save Tone.

306
00:21:48,530 --> 00:21:49,531
Come on, honey.

307
00:21:52,822 --> 00:21:53,823
Let's go.

308
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,240
Duang, I will drive this car back.

309
00:21:55,952 --> 00:21:56,953
Yes, sir.

310
00:22:48,499 --> 00:22:49,500
Perm?

311
00:22:51,139 --> 00:22:52,480
Where did you find her?

312
00:22:53,144 --> 00:22:54,560
I found her at a friend's house.

313
00:22:56,675 --> 00:22:58,104
She was mad at me

314
00:22:58,195 --> 00:22:59,491
but now we made up.

315
00:23:00,504 --> 00:23:03,200
Why were you so mad at him about that you ran away from home?

316
00:23:03,776 --> 00:23:06,100
If something happened with my grandchild, you will be in big trouble.

317
00:23:08,182 --> 00:23:09,183
Where is Tone?

318
00:23:09,467 --> 00:23:10,880
Why are there only the two of you here?

319
00:23:11,822 --> 00:23:13,650
I asked Tone to run some errands out of town.

320
00:23:14,504 --> 00:23:15,800
He won't be back for a while.

321
00:23:17,587 --> 00:23:18,588
Are you sure?

322
00:23:19,288 --> 00:23:19,909
What errands?

323
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:21,320
None of your f--king business!

324
00:23:23,675 --> 00:23:25,526
Nobody can ask me anything about this anymore.

325
00:23:26,710 --> 00:23:27,720
It is over now.

326
00:24:19,632 --> 00:24:20,633
Shen.

327
00:24:22,798 --> 00:24:24,360
Can you love me like you normally do?

328
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:29,200
From now on,

329
00:24:30,203 --> 00:24:33,170
I will take good care of you and the baby.

330
00:24:33,603 --> 00:24:36,650
Let bygones be bygones.

331
00:24:40,136 --> 00:24:42,600
I will be nice to you, talk to you nicely

332
00:24:43,686 --> 00:24:44,687
and I will

333
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:47,040
cherish and nourish

334
00:24:48,630 --> 00:24:50,000
both of you so well.

335
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:54,080
Do you expect me to believe you,

336
00:24:55,110 --> 00:24:57,880
when everything you did to me was quite the opposite?

337
00:24:58,016 --> 00:24:59,440
It's because I had to.

338
00:25:00,598 --> 00:25:02,920
Tone already told you about the will.

339
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:09,680
I needed to do anything to push you to him.

340
00:25:10,563 --> 00:25:11,760
I needed to abuse you physically

341
00:25:11,902 --> 00:25:13,040
and mentally. I was mean to you

342
00:25:13,140 --> 00:25:15,041
even though I didn't want to.

343
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:17,960
I love you so much, do you know that?

344
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:22,680
But I can't give my love to you like you expected me to.

345
00:25:26,128 --> 00:25:28,729
- I think you love your dad's assets more than me.
- Damn it.

346
00:25:34,086 --> 00:25:35,760
We can't live without them.

347
00:25:37,862 --> 00:25:40,080
No matter how much you love me, are you willing to live off of nothing

348
00:25:40,123 --> 00:25:41,180
like they did it in those romantic novels?

349
00:25:44,112 --> 00:25:45,840
I did all of that because I love you.

350
00:25:45,850 --> 00:25:47,200
I love you, I love you,

351
00:25:47,251 --> 00:25:48,640
I love you, please understand me.

352
00:25:48,771 --> 00:25:49,772
Hey,

353
00:25:50,488 --> 00:25:51,960
I'm sorry, Shen.

354
00:25:54,915 --> 00:25:55,916
I didn't mean to.

355
00:26:03,056 --> 00:26:04,840
I will improve myself.

356
00:26:13,414 --> 00:26:15,880
Tell me what is on your mind?

357
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:19,081
Talk to me.

358
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:21,361
Don't treat me this way.

359
00:26:21,961 --> 00:26:22,962
Come on.

360
00:26:23,870 --> 00:26:24,871
Talk!

361
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:26,360
I said to talk to me!

362
00:26:32,450 --> 00:26:34,320
I don't want to hurt your feeling if I say anything.

363
00:26:34,872 --> 00:26:35,873
Then don't say it.

364
00:26:37,374 --> 00:26:38,900
Haven't I been hurt enough?

365
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:40,120
You don't think I was hurt too?

366
00:26:42,040 --> 00:26:45,011
- You don't think that I was hurt?
- My pain is much more worse than yours.

367
00:26:48,931 --> 00:26:50,400
How do you know?

368
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:54,680
How do you know about it?

369
00:26:55,219 --> 00:26:56,800
If you were in so much pain,

370
00:26:56,947 --> 00:26:59,331
why would you drag me to roll in this pain with you?

371
00:26:59,869 --> 00:27:01,160
You told me that you loved me,

372
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,190
- you wouldn't do that…
- I am more painful than you.

373
00:27:03,201 --> 00:27:04,560
There was no way you could me more painful than me.

374
00:27:11,668 --> 00:27:12,669
Do you want to see it?

375
00:27:14,523 --> 00:27:15,680
See how painful I am?

376
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:25,240
Tone only knows that my part couldn't work properly.

377
00:27:26,019 --> 00:27:28,160
But it is more than than, Shen. It is worse than that.

378
00:27:31,091 --> 00:27:32,640
Why don't you take a look of how painful I am?

379
00:27:36,590 --> 00:27:37,591
See that?

380
00:27:39,934 --> 00:27:41,480
It was all cut off, all of it!

381
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:46,561
Look!

382
00:27:52,744 --> 00:27:53,745
See?

383
00:27:55,960 --> 00:27:57,560
You don't even want to look at it.

384
00:28:00,566 --> 00:28:02,040
But I have to live with it.

385
00:28:04,694 --> 00:28:06,320
I have to live with it for the rest of my life.

386
00:28:28,966 --> 00:28:30,321
Do you understand me now?

387
00:28:32,923 --> 00:28:34,320
You must feel sorry for me.

388
00:28:36,078 --> 00:28:37,079
You must forgive me.

389
00:28:39,310 --> 00:28:42,400
You are the only one who can heal my pain.

390
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:47,800
Can we go back to normal?

391
00:28:50,408 --> 00:28:51,409
Please? Love me?

392
00:29:07,299 --> 00:29:08,300
It's fine.

393
00:29:10,019 --> 00:29:11,600
It's okay if you can't accept me now.

394
00:29:15,299 --> 00:29:17,801
I will be nice to you until you would love me back.

395
00:29:24,752 --> 00:29:26,960
But I need to warn you.

396
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,080
Don't you dare running away from me

397
00:29:30,700 --> 00:29:32,360
or tell anything about the secret.

398
00:29:33,254 --> 00:29:35,560
Remember that Tone's life is in the palm of my hand.

399
00:29:36,075 --> 00:29:38,400
I can order him to be dead or alive.

400
00:29:44,146 --> 00:29:46,680
You should rest, my dear.

401
00:31:03,984 --> 00:31:04,985
You can put them there.

402
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:11,881
Thank you so much.

403
00:31:13,056 --> 00:31:14,400
If my wife is getting better,

404
00:31:14,457 --> 00:31:16,120
I can be back to the department.

405
00:31:16,864 --> 00:31:17,900
It's quite alright, sir.

406
00:31:18,656 --> 00:31:20,331
We wouldn't mind coming here to work.

407
00:31:20,398 --> 00:31:21,883
It's not much of a burden.

408
00:31:23,430 --> 00:31:24,431
Thank you.

409
00:31:25,040 --> 00:31:27,200
You two can find something to eat in the kitchen.

410
00:31:27,241 --> 00:31:28,520
I already told Erb to prepare something for you.

411
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:30,401
Thank you, sir.

412
00:31:40,368 --> 00:31:41,189
Mr. Perm,

413
00:31:41,203 --> 00:31:43,360
where do you want me to put Ms. Shen's bag, sir?

414
00:31:44,224 --> 00:31:45,920
Put it there, I will get it to her myself.

415
00:31:46,283 --> 00:31:47,284
Yes, sir.

416
00:32:35,566 --> 00:32:36,920
Please check her thoroughly.

417
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:40,320
She went out of town to visit her relatives

418
00:32:40,571 --> 00:32:41,840
and the route was so rough.

419
00:32:42,032 --> 00:32:43,840
I'm worried it could affect her health.

420
00:32:48,086 --> 00:32:49,280
There is nothing to worry about.

421
00:32:49,870 --> 00:32:51,260
They are both healthy.

422
00:32:51,825 --> 00:32:54,560
You can take your prenatal vitamins that I prescribed for you.

423
00:32:57,486 --> 00:32:58,487
Thank you so much.

424
00:32:59,004 --> 00:33:00,600
You're welcome.

425
00:33:01,174 --> 00:33:02,816
Right, sir?

426
00:33:03,568 --> 00:33:05,680
Dr. Smith sent me a letter from Penang.

427
00:33:05,974 --> 00:33:07,680
He asked me to send you his regards.

428
00:33:08,016 --> 00:33:10,850
He also asked if your wound was already healed.

429
00:33:11,472 --> 00:33:13,880
Wound? What wound?

430
00:33:14,438 --> 00:33:16,400
I don't know. I was confused as well.

431
00:33:16,662 --> 00:33:18,920
You said that you never went to see Dr. Smith.

432
00:33:19,312 --> 00:33:21,120
Why did he ask me about you?

433
00:33:26,520 --> 00:33:28,400
Right, I remember it now.

434
00:33:28,846 --> 00:33:31,160
It could be one of my subordinates who went to see the doctor.

435
00:33:31,534 --> 00:33:33,920
He could mention that he worked with me

436
00:33:34,662 --> 00:33:36,240
and it could be miscommunication.

437
00:33:36,300 --> 00:33:38,480
That's why Dr. Smith believed that he was me.

438
00:33:38,843 --> 00:33:40,160
I see.

439
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:42,000
That's probably why.

440
00:33:42,304 --> 00:33:44,320
I should write him a letter to

441
00:33:44,330 --> 00:33:45,360
correct the information.

442
00:33:45,664 --> 00:33:46,665
I should get going.

443
00:34:06,600 --> 00:34:07,840
What is on your mind?

444
00:34:12,808 --> 00:34:14,320
Doctor? Doctor!

445
00:34:15,293 --> 00:34:16,294
Yeah?

446
00:34:19,982 --> 00:34:20,983
Please let me give you a ride.

447
00:34:22,222 --> 00:34:23,600
It's fine.

448
00:34:23,883 --> 00:34:25,800
- I already called three-wheelers.
- Please, let me give you a ride.

449
00:34:26,640 --> 00:34:29,360
I want to discuss with you about my wife's and baby's health.

450
00:34:29,400 --> 00:34:30,700
We can discuss on the way.

451
00:34:33,502 --> 00:34:34,503
Sure.

452
00:34:35,203 --> 00:34:36,204
After you, sir.

453
00:34:43,336 --> 00:34:44,760
I feel bad for Ms. Shen.

454
00:34:45,230 --> 00:34:47,320
If she hadn't had enough, she wouldn't have run away from home.

455
00:34:47,891 --> 00:34:48,892
I know, right?

456
00:34:48,947 --> 00:34:50,948
It's too bad that Mr. Perm caught her and brought her back.

457
00:34:53,240 --> 00:34:55,200
Tone was gone. You don't think that

458
00:34:55,317 --> 00:34:57,720
he needed to run errands like Mr. Perm said, do you?

459
00:35:00,091 --> 00:35:02,800
I don't want to find out the truth.

460
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:05,200
I just know that

461
00:35:05,408 --> 00:35:06,800
I feel bad for Ms. Shen.

462
00:35:08,592 --> 00:35:09,593
And..

463
00:35:10,128 --> 00:35:13,160
if Tone got involved with this,

464
00:35:13,584 --> 00:35:15,170
I feel bad for him too.

465
00:35:21,723 --> 00:35:22,524
Let's go.

466
00:35:22,603 --> 00:35:24,700
We should made some delicious sweets for her

467
00:35:24,820 --> 00:35:25,821
so she would feel better.

468
00:35:30,678 --> 00:35:32,880
What are they hovering at?

469
00:35:33,440 --> 00:35:35,320
How could I know? I'm right here with you.

470
00:35:36,041 --> 00:35:37,042
Let's go and have a look.

471
00:35:54,219 --> 00:35:55,720
What? Somebody's dead?

472
00:35:56,099 --> 00:35:57,880
I think so, who's that?

473
00:35:59,046 --> 00:36:00,440
They said that he was a doctor.

474
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:09,561
Dr. Boonsong?

475
00:36:17,886 --> 00:36:18,887
Shen,

476
00:36:19,976 --> 00:36:20,977
why are you here?

477
00:36:21,341 --> 00:36:22,342
Why aren't you in your room?

478
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:24,240
It was so stuffy inside.

479
00:36:24,685 --> 00:36:26,080
I'm just getting some fresh air.

480
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:28,121
Is there a problem?

481
00:36:28,835 --> 00:36:30,640
I can't even sit in the garden?

482
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:34,401
Sure, you can.

483
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:37,180
Of course, you can sit in the garden.

484
00:36:53,512 --> 00:36:54,513
Perm,

485
00:36:58,104 --> 00:36:59,105
and…

486
00:37:00,035 --> 00:37:01,400
how is Tone doing?

487
00:37:02,030 --> 00:37:04,440
It's been two days that I haven't heard from him.

488
00:37:06,936 --> 00:37:08,080
Are you worried about him?

489
00:37:09,630 --> 00:37:10,631
He's still in prison.

490
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:12,400
He's waiting for the judge to make a decision.

491
00:37:16,083 --> 00:37:17,484
But I talked to him.

492
00:37:18,250 --> 00:37:21,051
He won't face death sentence but he will still be in jail.

493
00:37:23,235 --> 00:37:24,360
Remember that

494
00:37:26,067 --> 00:37:27,700
as long as you live her

495
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:29,840
and do what I say,

496
00:37:32,800 --> 00:37:34,520
Tone will still be alive.

497
00:37:44,702 --> 00:37:46,120
I'm glad that you two are here.

498
00:37:47,100 --> 00:37:48,600
You need to keep her company

499
00:37:48,832 --> 00:37:50,160
and you need to watch her, don't let her go anywhere.

500
00:37:50,498 --> 00:37:51,499
Yes, sir.

501
00:38:04,299 --> 00:38:05,300
Ms. Shen.

502
00:38:05,568 --> 00:38:07,160
There is a drama near the market.

503
00:38:07,707 --> 00:38:08,708
What is it?

504
00:38:11,307 --> 00:38:12,998
Dr. Boonsong was murdered.

505
00:38:13,062 --> 00:38:14,063
Huh?

506
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:16,400
He's dead?

507
00:38:16,533 --> 00:38:17,534
That's right.

508
00:38:17,678 --> 00:38:18,679
Who did it?

509
00:38:19,707 --> 00:38:20,720
We have no idea.

510
00:38:21,024 --> 00:38:23,120
People said that he was dead since yesterday evening.

511
00:38:23,446 --> 00:38:25,040
It means that after he left our house,

512
00:38:25,050 --> 00:38:26,480
he was murdered right away.

513
00:38:49,024 --> 00:38:50,200
What is on your mind?

514
00:38:55,158 --> 00:38:56,159
Doctor?

515
00:39:33,195 --> 00:39:34,480
You need to go to the market

516
00:39:35,520 --> 00:39:37,080
and drop this in a postbox.

517
00:39:38,336 --> 00:39:40,700
Do not look at the recipient's name.

518
00:39:41,779 --> 00:39:43,720
And do not let anyone in this house see it.

519
00:39:44,370 --> 00:39:45,371
- Yes, ma'am.
- Yes, ma'am.

520
00:39:46,318 --> 00:39:48,240
I can trust both of you, can't I?

521
00:39:49,987 --> 00:39:50,988
- Yes, ma'am.
- Yes, ma'am.

522
00:39:58,548 --> 00:40:00,680
Juang, do you think

523
00:40:01,214 --> 00:40:03,640
Ms. Shen wrote a letter to…?

524
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:07,520
Oh my! Why did she have to make a secret out of this?

525
00:40:08,430 --> 00:40:10,880
I've thought about it but I should say it out loud.

526
00:40:29,103 --> 00:40:31,520
Chan, do you think a man behind us is following us?

527
00:40:31,736 --> 00:40:33,720
I think so. I've been watching him for a while.

528
00:40:33,886 --> 00:40:35,760
We should turn this way to see if he's still following us.

529
00:40:47,166 --> 00:40:48,920
He is not following us, we're just paranoid.

530
00:40:58,499 --> 00:41:00,211
- It's me.
- Tone!

531
00:41:04,992 --> 00:41:06,840
Oh my goodness.

532
00:41:06,981 --> 00:41:08,520
Is it that bad?

533
00:41:09,995 --> 00:41:11,920
You're out of the prison.

534
00:41:12,139 --> 00:41:13,940
Are you prison-breaking?

535
00:41:18,016 --> 00:41:20,250
They tried to transfer me from Bang Kwang to Lad Yao

536
00:41:20,998 --> 00:41:22,360
along with four prisoners.

537
00:41:23,256 --> 00:41:25,040
But the bus crashed along the way

538
00:41:26,550 --> 00:41:27,720
so I escaped.

539
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:32,360
I stole someone's clothes to disguise.

540
00:41:32,494 --> 00:41:33,495
Oh my!

541
00:41:34,014 --> 00:41:36,480
So the officers are after you, right?

542
00:41:37,715 --> 00:41:38,716
I think so.

543
00:41:41,870 --> 00:41:43,840
I want to run away with Ms. Shen, far from here

544
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:46,720
so nobody can find us.

545
00:41:48,958 --> 00:41:50,680
Can you help bringing her out here?

546
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:54,080
It's so tough.

547
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:57,280
Mr. Perm is watching her every step.

548
00:41:59,477 --> 00:42:01,920
Actually, we went to the market

549
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:04,840
because Ms. Shen wanted us to drop the letter.

550
00:42:05,480 --> 00:42:07,400
She asked us not to look at the recipient.

551
00:42:08,080 --> 00:42:09,081
But I think…

552
00:42:11,768 --> 00:42:12,769
you should have a look.

553
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:18,100
[Recipient : Tone Chartchartree, Bang Kwang Central Prison]

554
00:42:25,926 --> 00:42:28,880
My dearest Mr. Tone,

555
00:42:30,320 --> 00:42:31,640
How are you?

556
00:42:32,520 --> 00:42:34,120
Is it tough for you inside?

557
00:42:35,195 --> 00:42:38,120
I'm doing fine so don't worry about me,

558
00:42:39,781 --> 00:42:41,650
except my heart. It doesn't feel great.

559
00:42:42,837 --> 00:42:44,640
It misses you every minute.

560
00:42:45,446 --> 00:42:47,080
I can't eat and I can't sleep.

561
00:42:47,894 --> 00:42:49,600
I'm worried that they would do something to you.

562
00:42:50,488 --> 00:42:52,640
We're in different jails

563
00:42:53,662 --> 00:42:56,640
but I feel like our hearts can be connected.

564
00:42:58,376 --> 00:42:59,920
I hope you are safe in there.

565
00:43:00,950 --> 00:43:03,360
I will take a good care of myself,

566
00:43:04,827 --> 00:43:07,160
waiting for us to meet again,

567
00:43:07,800 --> 00:43:08,801
all three of us,

568
00:43:09,195 --> 00:43:11,800
father, mother and baby.

569
00:43:12,760 --> 00:43:14,360
I love you with all my heart.

570
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:17,760
Yours truly, Shen.

571
00:43:22,248 --> 00:43:23,249
Ms. Shen.

572
00:43:26,947 --> 00:43:28,560
I need to get her out of the house.

573
00:44:54,341 --> 00:44:55,440
I'm hugging you,

574
00:44:55,744 --> 00:44:56,745
aren't you going to smile?

575
00:44:58,357 --> 00:45:00,960
I know that you've been in this stage for almost a year

576
00:45:01,115 --> 00:45:02,600
and you can't wait to be gone.

577
00:45:03,576 --> 00:45:05,960
But you can't go, I won't let you go.

578
00:45:07,368 --> 00:45:09,240
Your daughter-in-law is back

579
00:45:09,758 --> 00:45:11,600
and you have to wait until she gives birth,

580
00:45:12,480 --> 00:45:14,560
then you can finally rest in peace.

581
00:45:20,880 --> 00:45:22,160
You can't be mad at me.

582
00:45:22,344 --> 00:45:23,560
I have to play along with

583
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:25,080
the rules in that stupid will.

584
00:45:30,920 --> 00:45:32,720
You need to know that

585
00:45:33,315 --> 00:45:35,160
all of this happens

586
00:45:35,760 --> 00:45:37,161
because of you.

587
00:45:37,360 --> 00:45:38,361
It's all because of you.

588
00:45:57,125 --> 00:45:58,960
What did you talk to Dad about?

589
00:46:00,896 --> 00:46:01,897
None of your business.

590
00:46:03,856 --> 00:46:05,160
You're so full of secret nowadays.

591
00:46:23,385 --> 00:46:24,386
Shen,

592
00:46:25,457 --> 00:46:26,600
why are you sitting here for?

593
00:46:29,528 --> 00:46:30,800
I'm waiting for Chan and Juang,

594
00:46:31,096 --> 00:46:33,050
I asked them to buy me mangoes and they haven't been back.

595
00:46:34,131 --> 00:46:35,280
Where are you off to?

596
00:46:36,694 --> 00:46:37,720
Have a seat and talk to me.

597
00:46:41,168 --> 00:46:42,200
I want to talk to you nicely.

598
00:46:44,374 --> 00:46:45,375
Have a seat.

599
00:46:52,403 --> 00:46:53,440
Can I ask you something?

600
00:46:54,771 --> 00:46:56,160
What are you and my brother fighting about?

601
00:46:56,760 --> 00:46:58,100
Why did you run away from home?

602
00:46:59,502 --> 00:47:02,200
It's a couple's business, not other's business.

603
00:47:04,707 --> 00:47:05,708
I'm nosy.

604
00:47:09,360 --> 00:47:10,960
Or are you worried about the fact that

605
00:47:12,155 --> 00:47:13,160
you're not carrying my brother's baby?

606
00:47:16,635 --> 00:47:17,720
What are you talking about?

607
00:47:18,150 --> 00:47:19,440
Just tell me,

608
00:47:20,560 --> 00:47:21,720
who is the father of your baby?

609
00:47:23,174 --> 00:47:24,280
It's your brother's,

610
00:47:24,851 --> 00:47:26,000
who else could it be?

611
00:47:29,021 --> 00:47:30,040
I'm just checking.

612
00:47:31,771 --> 00:47:34,360
I saw you went out with Tone all the time.

613
00:47:38,126 --> 00:47:39,127
What are you two chatting about?

614
00:47:40,360 --> 00:47:41,480
You know, this and that.

615
00:47:43,022 --> 00:47:44,023
Nothing much.

616
00:47:50,363 --> 00:47:51,720
What did Term ask you?

617
00:47:54,688 --> 00:47:56,100
He asked me

618
00:47:56,800 --> 00:47:58,440
about the father of my baby.

619
00:48:00,803 --> 00:48:01,840
What did you say to him?

620
00:48:07,302 --> 00:48:08,700
I told him that it is yours, of course.

621
00:48:11,590 --> 00:48:13,320
- Are you sure?
- I am sure.

622
00:48:14,395 --> 00:48:15,396
Why are you asking?

623
00:48:16,400 --> 00:48:17,401
You don't trust me?

624
00:48:21,100 --> 00:48:22,440
If you don't trust me,

625
00:48:23,432 --> 00:48:25,960
are you willing to live with me who give you anxiety all the time?

626
00:48:29,163 --> 00:48:30,164
Come here.

627
00:48:55,867 --> 00:48:57,912
From now on, you will stay only in the bedroom

628
00:48:58,072 --> 00:48:59,600
and you can't go anywhere until giving birth.

629
00:49:00,400 --> 00:49:02,600
I am a human, I'm not an animal.

630
00:49:02,744 --> 00:49:03,962
You can't keep me in here.

631
00:49:04,216 --> 00:49:07,240
Don't look at me like that, I've never seen you as an animal.

632
00:49:08,850 --> 00:49:11,555
I just want to protect you from mean persons in the house,

633
00:49:11,736 --> 00:49:12,737
and that's all.

634
00:49:14,488 --> 00:49:15,489
Mean persons?

635
00:49:16,019 --> 00:49:18,040
Or someone who will seek the truth from me?

636
00:49:19,600 --> 00:49:22,680
Don't you ever forget that if my secret leaks, Tone will be dead.

637
00:49:44,515 --> 00:49:45,520
I'm sorry, honey.

638
00:49:47,107 --> 00:49:48,108
I'm sorry.

639
00:49:48,888 --> 00:49:49,889
You can't

640
00:49:50,696 --> 00:49:52,600
make me mad like this, okay?

641
00:49:54,867 --> 00:49:57,160
Perm!

642
00:49:58,118 --> 00:50:00,560
You can't keep me in here. Open the door!

643
00:50:00,672 --> 00:50:01,673
Open the door!

644
00:50:02,240 --> 00:50:05,000
Perm! Open the door!

645
00:50:18,579 --> 00:50:20,467
Perm, what is going on?

646
00:50:20,776 --> 00:50:21,777
What happens?

647
00:50:23,992 --> 00:50:25,520
I don’t want Shen to walk around,

648
00:50:26,686 --> 00:50:28,390
I'm worried that it could affect the baby.

649
00:50:28,702 --> 00:50:30,080
She tripped and almost fell earlier.

650
00:50:32,952 --> 00:50:34,000
We need to talk.

651
00:50:53,795 --> 00:50:55,800
What is going on between you and Shen?

652
00:50:57,054 --> 00:50:59,203
What are you two fighting about? Can you tell me?

653
00:51:04,387 --> 00:51:05,388
We're just...

654
00:51:06,696 --> 00:51:07,840
fire and ice, you know?

655
00:51:08,760 --> 00:51:10,600
It's normal for a couple to fight, don't you think?

656
00:51:10,661 --> 00:51:11,662
It's nothing big.

657
00:51:12,475 --> 00:51:14,480
But you keep her in the bedroom like that.

658
00:51:14,907 --> 00:51:16,140
It seems huge to me.

659
00:51:17,568 --> 00:51:20,280
You can tell me your problem, maybe I can help.

660
00:51:20,528 --> 00:51:21,640
It really is nothing.

661
00:51:23,270 --> 00:51:25,480
I can handle my problem, I'm an adult.

662
00:51:44,696 --> 00:51:45,697
Perm,

663
00:51:46,824 --> 00:51:48,000
have you ever heard of this?

664
00:51:48,725 --> 00:51:49,801
They say that

665
00:51:51,907 --> 00:51:53,040
if we love someone,

666
00:51:54,019 --> 00:51:55,640
we need to let them go.

667
00:51:58,008 --> 00:51:59,320
If they come back to us,

668
00:52:00,318 --> 00:52:01,920
it means that they love us too.

669
00:52:03,560 --> 00:52:06,200
You are locking the door, trying to keep your wife inside

670
00:52:06,261 --> 00:52:07,262
and hoping that she will stay with you,

671
00:52:08,184 --> 00:52:10,360
I don't think either of you will be happy.

672
00:52:12,608 --> 00:52:14,280
- Let her go.
- No, I won't/

673
00:52:15,723 --> 00:52:17,040
I have a baby with her.

674
00:52:18,262 --> 00:52:19,560
How could I leave her?

675
00:52:22,091 --> 00:52:24,480
Please, I beg you. We need to drop this.

676
00:52:50,411 --> 00:52:52,200
What? Chain the door?

677
00:52:52,496 --> 00:52:53,497
That's right.

678
00:52:53,542 --> 00:52:54,950
I don't know how to send any news to her.

679
00:52:55,750 --> 00:52:56,760
I can't hold it any longer,

680
00:52:57,083 --> 00:52:58,880
I need to see Ms. Shen now.

681
00:52:59,939 --> 00:53:00,940
Open the gate for me.

682
00:53:28,752 --> 00:53:30,560
Chan, clear the path that way.

683
00:55:06,464 --> 00:55:07,465
Ms. Shen!

684
00:55:09,243 --> 00:55:10,244
Tone!

685
00:55:19,142 --> 00:55:20,360
Is that really you?

686
00:55:22,882 --> 00:55:24,560
Am I dreaming?

687
00:55:25,960 --> 00:55:26,961
Ths is me.

688
00:55:27,561 --> 00:55:28,562
It really is me.

689
00:55:28,960 --> 00:55:30,400
Your Mr. Tone.

690
00:55:44,499 --> 00:55:45,960
How did you get out of the prison?

691
00:55:46,480 --> 00:55:47,481
It's a story for another time.

692
00:55:48,392 --> 00:55:49,441
Don't you worry.

693
00:55:49,886 --> 00:55:51,720
I will get you out of here.

694
00:55:53,000 --> 00:55:54,720
But Perm chained the door.

695
00:55:55,453 --> 00:55:56,454
I know.

696
00:55:56,472 --> 00:55:57,520
We need to escape through the terrace.

697
00:55:58,203 --> 00:55:59,240
But not right now.

698
00:55:59,686 --> 00:56:01,760
- Why's that?
- It's too dangerous.

699
00:56:52,440 --> 00:56:54,560
Why are Term and Rayrai rushing to?

700
00:56:56,760 --> 00:56:59,120
Did the police call to report you about their progress?

701
00:56:59,416 --> 00:57:00,417
On Tone?

702
00:57:00,760 --> 00:57:01,761
What about him?

703
00:57:01,928 --> 00:57:05,080
From now on, I will make you a happy girl.
